Edition:
Quote: The government is nominally vested in the person of a chief, termed the Rangatira nui or Ariki, whose power is derived either from a remote ancestry, marriage with the daughter of a powerful chieftain, or from having raised himself by reckless acts of valour and superior sagacity in native councils above the several competitors for the suffrages of his tribe.
